Kolo Toure left Anfield the happier sibling as Liverpool defeated younger brother Yaya’s Manchester City on Sunday.

Kolo’s late appearance in the game was a special one as it was the first time the Ivory Coast duo had gone head-to-head in a competitive game.

Before the lunchtime kick off Yaya tweeted: Love my big bro. He has taught me so much. But today… May the best Toure... sorry team win.’

