However, a 2-1 defeat to Liverpool probably wasn’t what Yaya had in mind as Manchester City slipped up yet again in their pursuit of the title.

A wonder goal in each half, either side of an Edin Dzeko strike, handed Liverpool all three points as Brendan Rodgers’ side continue to stake their claim for Champions League qualification.

Despite the defeat Yaya and Kolo showed their brotherly love at the full time whistle as they walked off the pitch together.

